1ea2b80d-9ad6-440e-9f40-4a8df83bdcb9.392878b6-73be-47a0-8857-60b49b8b2c62.description=
This is an operation that ask the user if the flow execution should go to success or not and based on the selection the flow goes to success or failure.

Inputs\:
    goToSucces - required input that can be used to decide the final execution of the flow\: success or failure.
    Field_1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    Field_2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    Field_3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    Field_4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
    success
    failure
1ea2b80d-9ad6-440e-9f40-4a8df83bdcb9.a54805c7-a900-46c7-a62a-48201dee049a.callout=To create a flow, delete the Success or Failure step and then find the operations that you want in the Dependencies tree and Projects tree to the left and drag them onto this canvas. Wire them together to create a flow. Save the flow and then execute it in Operations Orchestration Central. 1ea2b80d-9ad6-440e-9f40-4a8df83bdcb9.description=
Use this template when you are creating a new flow. You should remove the Success or Failure step.

Responses\:
    success - the flow completed successfully.
    failure - the flow completed unsuccessfully.
